definitions.definition: Portable cases, large bags, and similar equipment for manually carrying, pushing, or pulling personal items while traveling
examples: Please put your baggage in the trunk.

definitions.definition: Factors, especially psychological ones, which interfere with a person's ability to function effectively.
examples: This person has got a lot of emotional baggage .

definitions.definition: and uncountable ) An army's portable equipment; its baggage train .

main_definition: ( uncountable ) Portable cases, large bags, and similar equipment for manually carrying, pushing, or pulling personal items while traveling
secondary_definitions: ( uncountable , informal ) Factors, especially psychological ones, which interfere with a person's ability to function effectively.
( military , countable (obsolete) and uncountable ) An army's portable equipment; its baggage train .
